      "rationale": "Pressure head governs pump operating point selection; RH index directly quantifies hemolysis relative to predicate; peak WSS drives erythrocyte membrane stress via Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. All three QoIs are primary determinants of clinical hemolysis risk. Relevance exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
