    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out under MRL 2 provisions. Validation results VR-01 through VR-03 demonstrate adequate agreement between CFD predictions and experimental measurements for pressure head, relative hemolysis index, and wall shear stress. Parametric uncertainty quantification confirms RH < 1 criterion satisfied across the geometric tolerance space. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the defined COU.",
